snippet: A federal jury in Tennessee delivered a split verdict on Friday against nine people, mostly Somali men, who were accused of operating a sex trafficking ring in three states.
abstract: Federal jury in Tennessee delivers a split verdict against nine people, mostly Somali men, who were accused of operating a sex trafficking ring spanning from Minnesota to Ohio and Tennessee; three men are convicted and six men are acquitted.
lead_paragraph: A federal jury in Tennessee delivered a split verdict on Friday against nine people, mostly Somali men, who were accused of operating a sex trafficking ring in three states.

headline.main: Tennessee: Split Verdict in Sex Trafficking Case
headline.print_headline: Tennessee: Split Verdict In Sex Trafficking Case
